    eyebrow="His Holiness"
    title="About Sri Yogi"
    lead="Sri Sahasrara Yogishwara Swami Mahapeetam — the Eternal Golden Tree of the Avadhoota Siddha tradition, since 596 AD."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">

      <img src="/images/sri-yogi-portrait.jpg" alt="His Holiness Sri Sri Sri Yogishwara Swami"
           style="width:100%;border-radius:var(--radius);box-shadow:var(--shadow);margin-bottom:2rem;" />

      <h2>Birth and Spiritual Heritage</h2>
      <p>
        Sri Yogi was born on August 18, 1975, in Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala, a
        sacred region associated with Sree Padmanabhaswamy. This area is rich in
        spiritual significance, with a long-standing tradition established by
        Sri Atmarama Swami in 596 AD, which continues to shape the temples and
        spiritual centers today. Sri Yogi's family plays an essential role in this
        lineage, as many of his ancestors, including sadhus and rishis, have
        attained Samadhi at esteemed temples, thereby preserving the spiritual
        legacy into the present.
      </p>

      <h2>Early Life and Struggles</h2>
      <p>
        Sri Yogi spent his formative years in various family residences. His first
        home was with his great-grandmother at Moopanvilakam, Murukkumpuzha. He
        later moved to his grandfather's house in Thopil, Murukkumpuzha, where he
        lived until the age of three. When he turned four, the family established
        their own home in Murukkumpuzha.
      </p>
      <!-- IMAGE 1.png went here -->
      <p>
        At the age of seven, Sri Yogi was diagnosed with epilepsy, which
        significantly impacted his physical and mental well-being. He received
        treatment at the Government Medical College in Thiruvananthapuram. However,
        by the time he reached nine, his condition had deteriorated, and he faced a
        near collapse.
      </p>
      <!-- IMAGE 2.png went here -->

      <h2>Spiritual Transformation</h2>
      <p>
        During his challenging health journey, Sri Yogi encountered two
        transformative sadhus who profoundly changed the trajectory of his life.
        With the steadfast support of his mother, grandmother, and great-grandmother,
        he embarked on a quest for spirituality. At the tender age of ten, Sri Yogi
        began his search for the Divine Goddess Kali, which ultimately led him to his
        Guru, Srimath Paramahamsa Ananda Sri Sri Kalidasa Swami, in Pillathadam,
        Maruthwamalai, Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu.
      </p>
      <p>
        Under his Guru's guidance, Sri Yogi not only conquered his medical challenges
        but also attained spiritual enlightenment. By the age of fifteen, he developed
        divine vision, allowing him to foresee events concerning his family's future.
        In pursuit of deeper wisdom, he spent six months and seven and a half days in
        Samadhi under the mentorship of the renowned Siddha, Kalidasa Swami. Kalidasa
        Swami advised him to fulfill his worldly responsibilities before fully
        embracing the spiritual path, prompting Sri Yogi to work abroad while
        nurturing his spiritual growth.
      </p>

      <h2>Education &amp; Professional Life</h2>
      <p>
        Before fully embracing the spiritual path, Sri Yogi lived a remarkably
        accomplished worldly life. He is a multifaceted professional with a dynamic
        career spanning architecture, design, education, entrepreneurship, and
        wellness. With over two decades of diverse experience across India, the UAE,
        and Switzerland, he has consistently demonstrated a commitment to excellence
        in both technical disciplines and community service.
      </p>
      <p>
        His academic journey began in India, where he earned a School Leaving
        Certificate in 1994, followed by a Diploma in Architecture Engineering in
        1996. He went on to complete a Bachelor of Architecture in 2004, and enriched
        his portfolio with two MBAs in Finance and Human Resource Development — one
        from Switzerland in 2006 and another from India in 2017.
      </p>
      <p>His passion for design led him to numerous certifications and diplomas in specialised areas:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>AutoCAD, 3D MAX, Graphic &amp; Interior Design, Animation, and Special Effects</li>
        <li>Certifications in Microsoft &amp; Revit software</li>
        <li>A Private Flying License and a Flight Radio Telephone Operator’s License, reflecting his interest in aviation</li>
        <li>A French Language Certificate</li>
        <li>Architect (BBMP)</li>
        <li>Certified in Community-Oriented Policing and Civilian Rifle Training</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Early Career (1996–1998)</h3>
      <p>
        Sri Yogi began his career with hands-on roles in hospitality, logistics, and
        retail in the UAE — including positions as a steward, store helper, and
        assistant F&amp;B controller in Al Ain.
      </p>

      <h3>Design &amp; Architecture (1999–2009)</h3>
      <p>
        He transitioned into architectural and design roles in Dubai, working as a
        draughtsman, 3D designer, and interior designer, ultimately rising to
        Conceptual Designer Manager by 2009.
      </p>

      <h3>Freelancing &amp; Entrepreneurship (2010–Present)</h3>
      <p>
        Since 2010, Sri Yogi has embraced freelancing and entrepreneurship. He has
        worked independently as an architect, served as Director and Chairperson of a
        private limited company, co-founded an architectural firm, and launched a
        medicine manufacturing unit. His ventures also include teaching as a professor
        at a leading college between 2016 and 2017.
      </p>

